Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.33,0:04:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:262331,264917}{\i1}Soon, the city of Paris\Nwas about to become a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:266001,271256}{\i1}In fear of losing homes and properties\Nafter being involved in battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.25,0:04:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:271256,274092}{\i1}the rich and powerful\Nstarted to seek shelter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.09,0:04:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:274092,279389}{\i1}and one after another\Nmigrated to the city of Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.72,0:04:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:280724,284728}Mommy,\Nwhere is everyone going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:284728,288565}The war is about to begin.\NThey're running away to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.56,0:04:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288565,290484}Are we going to move, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.48,0:04:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:290484,292653}I don't really want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.15,0:04:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:293153,297574}Even if we escaped,\Nwe don't have any villas to hide in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.32,0:05:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298325,301912}There is no place for us\Noutside of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.91,0:05:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:301912,306333}These people live in a world\Nthat is entirely different from ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.33,0:05:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:306333,310754}They don't care at all\Nwhat happens to this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.92,0:05:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:310921,312130}{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.13,0:05:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:312130,319388}{\i1}Only a limited number of people\Nhad a place to escape from war.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:319388,321723}{\i1}The Rostain family\Nwas among the lucky ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.39,0:05:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:326395,328522}Quick, quick, quick!\NNo time for dilly-dallying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.52,0:05:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:328522,331149}The Prussian army\Nis just around the corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.69,0:05:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:331692,334987}Remember,\Nonly the nobles' belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.15,0:05:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:340158,342452}I don't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:342452,343620}What a drag!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.66,0:05:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345664,348333}I guess it's time to say goodbye\Nto this house for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:348333,349126}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:351878,353672}Andréa… It's Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.09,0:06:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:362097,363682}I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.89,0:06:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:366893,368562}Outta my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.60,0:06:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:369605,372065}What… What are you doing, young lady?\NStop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.06,0:06:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:372065,375027}Now is not the time for the lectures.\NIt's Andréa! It's Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.19,0:06:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:375193,376737}Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376737,377696}Who do we have here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:377696,379031}Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.03,0:06:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379031,381658}Andréa… Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.20,0:06:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382200,385495}Ms. Isabelle…\NYou're just too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.03,0:06:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:386038,388248}Hello, Jeanne. I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.79,0:06:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:388790,390959}Young master!\NWhat am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.95,0:06:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:390959,395047}Young master is here.\NMaster! Milady! Mr. Andréa is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395047,396173}How have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.17,0:06:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:396173,398425}Stupid, stupid brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.42,0:06:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:398425,400969}Do you have any idea\Nhow worried I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.96,0:06:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:400969,404431}Hey, hey, Isabelle.\NWhat's with this messy reception?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.43,0:06:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:404431,408268}Haven't you made your debut\Nin high society and become a lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:409603,413106}That's right. I'm a lady now.\NIsn't that right, Mr. Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.31,0:06:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:413315,416652}Yes. You made\Nan excellent lady that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.72,0:07:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:451728,457734}It is a pity that we must part\Njust after our family has finally reunited.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.11,0:07:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:458110,461905}Father, you'll be safe\Nas long as you stay in Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.90,0:07:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:461905,464825}When we know\Nthat our family is safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.82,0:07:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:464825,467536}we'll feel much more confident\Non the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.53,0:07:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467536,470414}Right.\NBut don't do anything reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.41,0:07:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:470414,471915}I understand. We won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.91,0:07:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:471915,474209}Our goal is not to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:474209,476336}It is to protect Paris to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.50,0:08:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:477504,481299}Apropos, Victor. You will not be able\Nto see Geneviève for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.29,0:08:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:481299,486179}I was hoping you could\Nget married, even if just in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.51,0:08:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:486513,489015}Marriage? Now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489015,490767}Yes, that's exactly what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490767,493603}Young people have a tendency\Nof making fools of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493603,496022}If you get married,\Nyou will start to be cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.02,0:08:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:496022,498775}And caution in war\Nis at a premium.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.77,0:08:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:498775,501737}Victor, now might be\Nactually the best time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:501737,502946}What will you do
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.94,0:08:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:502946,506241}if your betrothed has a little fun\Non the side behind your back?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.24,0:08:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:506241,509911}But I am going to fight\Nat the front line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.91,0:08:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:509911,512372}If something were\Nto happen to me…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.37,0:08:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:512372,515709}Victor. I am a French man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:515709,520297}Do you think a French soldier's wife is afraid\Nthat her husband will die protecting France?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:520297,523425}I don't remember\Nraising my daughter in such a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:523425,526052}Women do change their mind\Nabout such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.18,0:08:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:528180,531516}{\i1}Isabelle felt uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.51,0:08:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531516,534019}{\i1}Isabelle knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:09:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534019,540275}{\i1}She knew that Geneviève had\Nanother lover besides Victor… Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:555957,557250}Isabelle…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.25,0:09:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:557250,559085}I can not help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.71,0:09:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:559711,561296}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:561296,563298}Poor Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.50,0:09:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:565509,566593}{\i1}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.59,0:09:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:566593,568637}{\i1}Why are you silent?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:568637,570472}{\i1}You're such a coward, sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.47,0:09:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:570472,572891}{\i1}Why don't you say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:573767,580816}{\i1}Geneviève's mind was now full of thoughts\Nabout her piano teacher, Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:615016,618228}You're the daughter\Nof a great landowner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:618228,622148}And I'm… a pianist who lives\Nin town on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.14,0:10:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:622148,624776}The worlds we live in\Nare too far apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.77,0:10:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:624776,627571}I don't have what it takes\Nto make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.57,0:10:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:627571,631992}You coward! I will…\NI will follow you wherever you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.99,0:10:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:631992,633702}There's nothing we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.70,0:10:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:633702,635954}Geneviève…\NThere's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.33,0:10:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:639332,642377}A wedding only in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.37,0:10:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:642377,644212}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.21,0:10:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:644212,645755}I take your daughter as my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.88,0:10:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:646882,649718}You finally made up your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.92,0:10:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:649926,653096}Congratulations, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.09,0:10:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:653096,655724}Very well.\NLet us have a toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:655724,656850}Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.85,0:10:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:656850,659561}I know I made you wait\Na bit too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.56,0:11:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659561,663732}But please believe me, I have been\Nthinking only of you all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.15,0:11:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:665150,668153}Geneviève.\NYou will marry me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.28,0:11:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679289,682500}{\i1}Isabelle, who knew\Nabout Geneviève's feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.50,0:11:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:682500,685503}{\i1}only stood there\Nand watched this scene in silence.
Comment: 0,0:11:28.75,0:11:28.75,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:688757,688757}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.82,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:711821,716201}The elite are all fleeing to their\Nnice safe properties in Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:716201,718703}Must be nice,\Nhaving a place to escape to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:12:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:718703,722540}What about us?\NWhere are we going to escape to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.54,0:12:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:722540,724501}Escape?\NYou better be kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.50,0:12:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:724501,728463}I was born and raised in this town.\NI am a proud Parisian.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.46,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:728463,730757}I won't let anybody\Nhave our city.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:730757,734094}Damn right!\NI'm not moving an inch from this city!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:734386,737931}I'll say one thing. I won't stay idle\Nwhen the Prussian army comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.93,0:12:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:737931,741726}Music to my ears. I'll fight\Nby your side when the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.89,0:12:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:741893,743186}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.02,0:12:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:744020,746856}Hey, everybody!\NWe are Parisians!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:746856,748566}Paris is our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.98,0:12:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:748984,749985}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.19,0:12:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:750193,752404}Who is going to defend our city?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:752404,753238}Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.23,0:12:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:753238,754155}The army?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.15,0:12:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:754155,755240}The politicians?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.24,0:12:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:755240,756157}The aristocrats?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.15,0:12:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:756157,757742}No. It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.74,0:12:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757742,759160}It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.16,0:12:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:759160,761746}We'll protect our city\Nby ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.74,0:12:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:761746,762914}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.91,0:12:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:762914,764916}We will be the ones\Nwho protect Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:764916,765917}It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.91,0:12:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:765917,767043}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.04,0:12:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:767043,767919}We'll defend it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.91,0:12:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:767919,768878}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.87,0:12:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:768878,769838}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.83,0:12:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769838,770922}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:770922,771631}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.63,0:12:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771631,773341}– Defend Paris!\N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.34,0:12:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773341,775844}Defend Paris!\NWe'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.84,0:12:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:775844,777262}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.26,0:12:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:777262,778888}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.68,0:13:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:779681,781683}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.68,0:13:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:781683,783518}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.51,0:13:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:783518,784978}{\fad(0,1468)}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.27,0:13:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:785270,787272}Exciting times, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.81,0:13:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:787814,791484}Yes. These are the real feelings\Nof those truly living in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:792318,797574}There is no love for Paris among the people\Nwho leave it and flee to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.78,0:13:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:797782,800994}I heard that the Rostain family\Nis evacuating there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.99,0:13:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:800994,801995}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.08,0:13:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:804080,806875}Must be nice, not having\Nto worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:810879,814090}Ordinary people have it\Nworse than ever these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.09,0:13:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:814090,815675}I'm a bit jealous of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.05,0:13:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:816051,818178}Cut it. Leave Geneviève out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.17,0:13:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:818178,820597}A relationship between us\Nis just not meant to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.43,0:13:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:823433,824976}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.22,0:13:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:825226,826853}You had too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:827312,828480}See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:828480,831191}Here comes the goddess savior\Nof the poor artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.40,0:13:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:834402,835653}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.71,0:14:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:853713,855131}Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.13,0:14:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:855131,856466}Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.46,0:14:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:856466,862180}That little boat is home to a family\Nwith God knows how many children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.85,0:14:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:866851,868394}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.39,0:14:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:868394,870897}Marry Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.89,0:14:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:870897,871981}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.98,0:14:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:871981,874692}Our relationship\Nis destined to fail, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:874859,876986}Why? Because our positions\Nare too different?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.98,0:14:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:876986,878696}The worlds we live in\Nare too far apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.69,0:14:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:878696,881074}I don't care about any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.07,0:14:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:881074,883159}Jules, I care only about you—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.15,0:14:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:883159,886996}I only want you to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.33,0:14:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:889332,891709}Stop it! I'm so sick of others\Nmaking decisions for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.04,0:14:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:892043,893419}I am a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.41,0:14:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893419,896047}Do not decide for me\Nwhat my happiness is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.04,0:14:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:896047,898716}I decide my own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:911271,913898}I want to live by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:913898,915984}I don't need anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.98,0:15:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:915984,918528}I'll throw everything else away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.69,0:15:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919696,920905}Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.78,0:15:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:921781,922866}Geneviève…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:924826,927579}I love you, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:927579,929080}Tell me not to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.59,0:15:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:941593,944304}Ms. Geneviève,\Nit is time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.89,0:15:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:948892,952896}Tomorrow I will go\Nand tell your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:15:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:957317,958443}Then, I'll be on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.90,0:16:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:962906,964115}Promise you'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.86,0:16:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:964866,965658}I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.99,0:16:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:966993,968995}Mr. Gaston,\Nwhat happened here…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.99,0:16:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:968995,972665}I am Ms. Geneviève's\Nfaithful servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.87,0:16:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:977879,979881}{\i1}Goodbye, Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.88,0:16:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:979881,982759}{\i1}Jules… I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.68,0:16:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:987680,990350}{\i1}Farewell, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.60,0:16:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:998608,1002195}{\i1}"We'll never meet again".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.19,0:16:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1002195,1006658}{\i1}Jules vowed inwardly,\Nlooking at the departing carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1044696,1046114}{\i1}Forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.50,0:17:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1059502,1060962}{\i1}Forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1060962,1063256}{\i1}I have to forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1071347,1075018}{\i1}There are other things\Nthat I must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1075018,1076185}{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.56,0:17:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076561,1079188}{\i1}We have to defend Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1079188,1080523}{\i1}I'll defend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.89,0:18:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1080898,1082734}{\i1}I'll defend Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.73,0:18:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1082734,1084736}{\i1}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1084736,1087155}{\i1}Defend Paris. Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.15,0:18:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1087155,1088906}{\i1}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1106799,1114015}It is very commendable that the citizens\Nof Paris are willing to take arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.01,0:18:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1114015,1118269}But I cannot say that\NI am really happy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1118519,1121898}What do you mean\Nby that, Mr. Thiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1121898,1126778}When the city of Paris becomes\Na battlefield, there will be fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.77,0:18:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126778,1130156}This means risk for\Nour homes and properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1130156,1133201}We must use whatever means\Nnecessary to prevent this risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.78,0:18:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133785,1135495}Our homes and properties?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.49,0:19:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1135495,1141459}Surely you don't mean that to protect these,\Nwe should give up without a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1141459,1144921}That is also a possibility, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.92,0:19:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1144921,1146589}I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.58,0:19:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1146589,1148633}Paris is the pride of all of France!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.63,0:19:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148633,1152762}Losing Paris is equivalent\Nto losing the heart of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.76,0:19:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1152762,1154972}I will never agree to that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.77,0:19:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1162772,1165608}I can't believe this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.56,0:19:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1166567,1168111}What happened, Mr. General?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.31,0:19:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1168319,1169612}He's gone nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.61,0:19:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1169612,1176411}The politicians want to protect their assets\Nand consider selling Paris to Prussia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.07,0:19:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1177078,1178371}Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.37,0:19:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1178371,1179372}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182166,1183543}Geneviève!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1183543,1185503}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.75,0:19:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1185753,1188798}I would like to talk\Nto Victor alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.67,0:19:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1189674,1194220}I don't mind, but don't abuse\Nyour privilege of being my sister too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.73,0:20:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1206732,1209694}What? You're not going\Nto Versailles? Geneviève…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.15,0:20:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1211154,1212029}I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.86,0:20:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1212864,1214490}I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.49,0:20:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1214490,1216159}I'm leaving our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.74,0:20:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1216742,1218703}Wait.\NWhat are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.87,0:20:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218870,1220371}Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.37,0:20:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1220371,1222748}Please forgive me.\NBut my heart is with Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.76,0:20:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1237763,1238723}Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.22,0:20:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1239223,1242310}I am Victor Langlois\Nof the French Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.31,0:20:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1242310,1243019}Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.23,0:20:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1248232,1250985}Jules Francoeur, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.98,0:20:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1250985,1251986}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.03,0:21:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1259035,1260369}I challenge you to a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270338,1272131}Marriage? With you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1273466,1276219}Naturally, not right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.21,0:21:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1276219,1278638}Just an engagement, for now.\NBut, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.63,0:21:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278638,1279972}Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.97,0:21:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1279972,1281766}I know we're\Nchildhood friends and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.76,0:21:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1281766,1284477}but how can you ask me\Nfor my hand so casually?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.72,0:21:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1284727,1288022}What? But this is\Nanything but casual.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.02,0:21:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1288022,1291108}I've asked you\Ncountless times, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.44,0:21:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1292443,1295071}Hey, when we grow up,\Nwe'll marry each other, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.07,0:21:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1295071,1298157}Nope. I'm not marrying\Nanyone like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.15,0:21:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1298157,1300618}Hey, when are we\Ngoing to marry?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1300618,1304330}Listen, I hate\Nweaklings and crybabies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.33,0:21:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1304330,1305623}Fine then!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.54,0:21:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1308543,1310127}What do you think\Nyou're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.17,0:21:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1313172,1314924}Oww!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.63,0:22:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1318636,1322265}Isabelle, your wedding dress\Nlooks so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.26,0:22:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1322265,1323724}Of course it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.72,0:22:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1323724,1326978}But you'll be disappointed,\Nsince I'll be wearing it for someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.81,0:22:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328813,1331274}No way… No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.57,0:22:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1339574,1345246}Do you remember that you\Neven agreed a few times?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.24,0:22:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1345246,1347540}I had to get rid of you somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.54,0:22:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1347540,1350376}Jean, stop living in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.37,0:22:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1350376,1352837}My answer is the same as before.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.83,0:22:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1352837,1354630}So you refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.00,0:22:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1355006,1356299}I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.29,0:22:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1356299,1357133}Come on…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.63,0:22:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1357633,1358217}Don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.21,0:22:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1358217,1359302}No means no!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.30,0:22:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1359302,1360136}– Come on…\N– Knock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.34,0:22:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1362346,1364140}I will withdraw for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.14,0:22:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1364140,1367643}We're going to live next\Nto each other in Versailles, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.64,0:22:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1367643,1369478}I'll be able to see you any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.47,0:22:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1369478,1371606}Versailles is a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.60,0:22:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1371606,1373316}Without you, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.31,0:22:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1373316,1375484}Your words can't hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.48,0:22:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1375484,1377236}You silly girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.07,0:23:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1379071,1380197}Geneviève!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.82,0:23:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1381824,1383117}Where is Geneviève?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.24,0:23:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1385244,1386996}Do you need anything, Andréa?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.78,0:23:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1387788,1390374}Victor challenged\NJules to a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.94,0:23:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1415941,1420821}{\i1}Victor and Jules…\Nwill duel each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.82,0:23:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1420821,1425034}{\i1}It was something Isabelle\Ncould hardly even imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.49,0:23:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1426494,1432541}{\i1}The adult world began to appear\Nin vivid colors around the 15-old Isabelle.
