Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.13,0:24:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1440132,1443677}I'm overjoyed to see my brother\NAndréa return home in safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.67,0:24:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1443677,1448182}But Victor and Jules…\Nare going to fight in a duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.47,0:24:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1448474,1451477}Victor is a soldier.\NHe's an expert shooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.47,0:24:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1451477,1454939}But Jules?\NHe's just a piano teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.93,0:24:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1454939,1456482}What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.48,0:24:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1456482,1459610}In addition, there's also\Nthe evacuation to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.73,0:24:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1460736,1463447}Next time on "Isabelle from Paris":
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.44,0:24:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1463447,1467409}"On The Day of The Duel, The One I Love…"\NPlease look forward to it.
